證券交易法專題研究（一）                


  	This course discusses fundamental principles, as well as advance ones, of securities regulation.  It is design mainly for graduate law students who have in-depth knowledge of corporate law and securities regulation.  It also serves as a review of Taiwan’s corporate law and securities regulation since they are akin to their American counterparts.  It provides an overview of the U.S. securities laws and regulation.  It furnishes advanced discussions of laws and practices in both Taiwan and the United States.  It also enables students to gain broader and deeper understandings of securities regulation in both jurisdictions, to develop their abilities to apply laws and regulation against any given factual circumstance, and to utilize their knowledge and understandings in their future disciplines.

課程教育目標 

B. 碩士班：配合經貿社會結構的發展 
課程基本素養與核心能力 

[基本素養]法學素養
[核心能力]同時具備科際整合的能力
 
